snippet.title: Eastern Collier Growth - Evenings at the Conservancy
snippet.description:
The presentation was given by Conservancy Director of Environmental Policy Nicole Johnson and Senior Environmental Planning Specialist April Olson. 

Now is a pivotal time in Collier County’s history. A huge area of eastern Collier County is vulnerable to intensive development. If the eastern lands are developed as currently planned, the county could add between 270,000 and 389,000 residents! Collier County currently has about 360,000 full-time residents.

Learn more here: https://www.conservancy.org/our-work/policy/eastern-collier-county
